  <datafield tag="545" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The NMEAC was founded in 1980 as a response to the Big Rock Nuclear Plant near Charlevoix, Michigan. Since them, the Council has devoted itself to transportation management, land use, contamination cleanup, and parkland protection.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The records document NMEAC's involvement in issues of land use, toxic cleanup, and transportation. Some specific issues addressed include conservation efforts on the Crystal and Boardman Rivers, cleanup of lands contaminated by the activities of corporate polluters, and the management of lands formerly occupied by the State Psychiatric Hospital and Asylum in Traverse City.</subfield>
  </datafield>
